## Defense-in-Depth Testing Pyramid

### The Pyramid Invariant

> **UT proves logic. IT proves wiring. E2E proves the journey.**

Each tier has a distinct purpose that cannot be replaced by another tier:

| Tier | Proves | Example |
|------|--------|---------|
| **UT** | Component logic in isolation | `MaterializeCRD` correctly creates a K8s resource from a pending config |
| **IT** | Component is wired into production code | `af_create_rr` after-callback triggers `MaterializeCRD` through the real dispatch path |
| **E2E** | Full user journey works end-to-end | Interactive session creates IS CRD only after first remediation request |

**A component with only UT coverage is NOT implemented -- it is prototyped.** GREEN phase is not complete until the IT test for every wiring point passes.

**See**: [Wiring Verification Rule](mdc:.cursor/rules/10-wiring-verification.mdc)

