## Test Tier Specifications

### Unit Tests

**Location**: Colocated with production code in `pkg/` and `internal/` (black-box `package <name>_test`).
**Execution**: `make test-unit-<service>` or `go test ./pkg/<service>/...`
**Framework**: Ginkgo/Gomega BDD (MANDATORY - no standard Go testing)

**Mock Strategy**:
```go
// Mock ONLY external dependencies
mockLLMProvider   *mocks.MockLLMProvider    // External: AI service
mockK8sClient     client.Client              // External: fake.NewClientBuilder()
mockVectorDB      *mocks.MockVectorDatabase  // External: Database

// Use REAL business logic components
workflowBuilder   *engine.IntelligentWorkflowBuilder
safetyFramework   *platform.SafetyFramework
```

### Integration Tests

**Location**: `test/integration/`
**Execution**: `make test-integration-[service]`
**Framework**: Ginkgo/Gomega BDD with envtest/KIND

Zero mocks for business logic. Real K8s API via envtest. Real databases via testcontainers. Mock ONLY external services (LLM, external APIs).

### E2E Tests

**Location**: `test/e2e/`
**Execution**: `make test-e2e-[service]`
**Framework**: Ginkgo/Gomega BDD with KIND/OCP clusters

Zero mocks for internal components. Real Kubernetes clusters. Mock LLM MAY be acceptable for test speed.

