## Mock Strategy

### What to Mock vs Keep Real

| Category | Action |
|----------|--------|
| **External APIs** (LLM, HolmesGPT, OpenAI) | Mock |
| **Databases** (PostgreSQL, Vector DB, Redis) | Mock in UT, real in IT |
| **Kubernetes API** | `fake.NewClientBuilder()` in UT, real in IT/E2E |
| **Network services** (external HTTP/gRPC) | Mock |
| **ALL business logic** (`pkg/` code) | Keep REAL |
| **ALL internal algorithms** | Keep REAL |
| **Configuration** | Use real config with test values |
| **Utilities** | Keep REAL |

### Mock Reuse Decision Matrix

| Component Type | Action |
|---------------|--------|
| **External Services** (AI, K8s, DB) | Use existing mocks from `pkg/testutil/mocks/` |
| **Business Logic** (Engine, Analytics) | Use REAL components |
| **Configuration** | Use real config with test values |
| **Utilities** | Use real utilities |

**Red flag**: >3 mocks in a single test. Use real business components instead.

